OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA rather cloudy start with some
OL,6,Fdrizzle on western hills. The cloud
OL,7,Fbreaking up to give some bright or
OL,8,Fsunny spells, especially in the east.
OL,9,FA band of rain will reach northern
OL,10,Fparts by late-afternoon, moving
OL,11,Fsoutheastwards. Windy. Staying mild.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA band of rain will clear
OL,14,Fsoutheastwards by evening, with some
OL,15,Fscattered showers following on behind.
OL,16,FBecoming dry with clear periods
OL,17,Fovernight. A touch of frost possible
OL,18,Fin rural spots.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
